===Etymology===
First attested in the 18th century, from {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|ogre|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|Orcus||god of the underworld|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|Όρκος|sc=polytonic|tr=Horkos|lang=grc}}, the personified demon of oaths ({{term|ὅρκος|sc=polytonic||oath|lang=grc}}) who inflicts punishment upon perjurers.

